Users
  1. Add a user
    adduser myusername```
  2. give sudo privileges
    sudo visudo
  3. remove default users (e.g. pi) <b>AFTER</b> you've logged in as a different user and verified sudo
    deluser -remove-home pi

Apache
  1. Install the apache server
    apt-get -y install apache2
  2. Set web permissions<br>
    a. set /var/www directory permissions
      sudo chgrp -R www-data /var/www
      sudo chmod -R 775 /var/www
      sudo chmod g+s /var/www
      sudo chgrp -R www-data /var/www/html
      sudo chmod -R 775 /var/www/html
      sudo chmod g+s /var/www/html
    b. add relevant users to www-data group
      sudo usermod -a -G www-data username
  3. Enable SSL:
    a2ensite default-ssl
    a2enmod ssl
  4. Change listening ports (unless you really like 80 and 443):
    vi /etc/apache2/ports.conf
    vi /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/default-ssl.conf
    vi /etc/apache2/sites-enabled/000-default.conf
  5. Generate self-signed SSL cert:
    openssl genrsa -aes256 -out myserver.key.secure 2048
    openssl rsa -in myserver.key.secure -out myserver.key
    openssl req -new -key myserver.key -out myserver.csr
    openssl x509 -req -days 730 -in myserver.csr -signkey myserver.key -out myserver.crt
    cp myserver.crt /etc/ssl/certs/
    cp myserver.key /etc/ssl/private/
    rm myserver.csr 
    rm myserver.key.secure 
  6. Restart apache
    service apache2 restart

MySQL:
  1. Install mysql server
    sudo apt-get -y install mysql-server
  2. Go into mysql
    mysql -u root -p
  3. Create user & set permissions
    CREATE USER 'myuser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'mypasswd';
    GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON *.* to 'myuser'@'localhost' WITH GRANT OPTION;

PHP:
  1. Install PHP CLI, PHP Apache Libraries and PHP-Mysql
    apt-get install php5-cli
    apt-get -y install libapache2-mod-php5
    apt-get install php5-mysql

NTFS support:
  1. install ntfs-3g (for rw access)

File Shares:
  1. Install samba
    apt-get install samba
  2. set a password for your user (this is different than the regular system passwords)
    sudo smbpasswd -a myusername
  3. vi /etc/samba/smb.conf  -- Append the following:
    [<sharename>]
    path=/path/to/share
    valid users = <usernames>
    read only = no
  4. Restart Samba
    service smbd restart
